{"TopicId":190495,"ForumId":104,"TopicTitle":"How do I create a mod?","CreatedByName":"Astrionix","CreatedById":201588,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-12-20T01:16:32Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Astrionix","CreatedById":201588,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-12-20T01:16:32Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027ve been thinking about creating some KSP mods for some time but, I don\u0027t really know where to start. One question I thought of so far is what kind of application(s) should I use? A couple mods that I\u0027ve thought of making are parts mods and mods that just change things in the game.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"HebaruSan","CreatedById":156657,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-12-20T02:54:00Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223719146\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022190495\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221576804592\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022201588\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Astrion\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, Astrion said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nwhat kind of application(s) should I use? A couple mods that I\u0027ve thought of making are parts mods\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFor parts mods you only need a text editor to create .cfg files to define your parts.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, Astrion said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nmods that just change things in the game.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDepending on which things you want to change, this may also only need ModuleManager and a text editor to create .cfg files:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedauthorid=\u002257146\u0022 data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed2601899196\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/50533-18x-module-manager-413-november-30th-2019-right-to-ludicrous-speed/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0022 style=\u0022height:211px;max-width:502px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOr you might need to write C# code.\u00A0Someone just asked about that a few weeks ago:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedauthorid=\u0022200196\u0022 data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed9025144339\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/190146-how-do-i-make-a-mod/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0022 style=\u0022height:189px;max-width:502px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n"}]}